🧪 QA Testing
Automated Employee Onboarding & Offboarding System

This section defines how to test the system end-to-end to ensure correct workflows, secure access control, and reliable data handling.

1. QA Testing Objectives

QA ensures:

Onboarding/offboarding workflows execute correctly
Access control is enforced (no unauthorized access)
Data is consistent and secure
Integrations (HR, IAM, email) work correctly
Audit logs are accurate and complete
2. Testing Types
2.1 Unit Testing

Tests individual components:

Employee creation
Role assignment
Access provisioning logic
Audit logging
2.2 Integration Testing

Validates system interactions:

HR system → Workflow engine
Workflow → IAM provisioning
Offboarding → access revocation
2.3 System Testing (End-to-End)

Simulates full lifecycle:

New hire → onboarding → active state
Exit request → offboarding → deactivated user
2.4 Security Testing
Unauthorized access attempts
Role escalation attempts
Token/session validation
API security checks
2.5 Regression Testing

Ensures new changes don’t break:

Existing workflows
Access control rules
Data retention logic
